Sets the value of errno.

# Example
```
use nix::errno::Errno;

Errno::EIO.set();

assert_eq!(Errno::last(), Errno::EIO);
```

249.docs:
A file descriptor referring to the working directory of the current process
**that should be ONLY passed to the `dirfd` argument of those `xxat()` functions**.

# Examples

Use it in [`openat()`]:

```no_run
use nix::fcntl::AT_FDCWD;
use nix::fcntl::openat;
use nix::fcntl::OFlag;
use nix::sys::stat::Mode;

let fd = openat(AT_FDCWD, "foo", OFlag::O_RDONLY | OFlag::O_CLOEXEC, Mode::empty()).unwrap();
```

# WARNING

Do NOT pass this symbol to non-`xxat()` functions, it won't work:

```should_panic
use nix::errno::Errno;
use nix::fcntl::AT_FDCWD;
use nix::sys::stat::fstat;

let never = fstat(AT_FDCWD).unwrap();
```

145.docs:
Sets the platform-specific errno to no-error

```
use nix::errno::Errno;

Errno::EIO.set();

Errno::clear();

let err = Errno::last();
assert_ne!(err, Errno::EIO);
assert_eq!(err, Errno::from_raw(0));
```

233.docs:
Safe wrappers around errno functions

# Example
```
use nix::errno::Errno;

Errno::EIO.set();
assert_eq!(Errno::last(), Errno::EIO);

Errno::clear();
assert_eq!(Errno::last(), Errno::from_raw(0));
```
